title: Area Football: Ridgewood defeats West Central 54-6
text: Posted Oct. 24, 2015 at 12:01 AM Posted Oct. 24, 2015 at 12:01 AM BIGGSVILLE â€” The Ridgewood football team ended its season with a 54-6 rout of West Central on Friday. The Spartans rolled to a 19-0 lead after the first quarter and led 32-0 at the break. The Heat scored their lone TD with 8:42 left to play. Ridgewood outgained West Central 412 yards to 99. The Heat were held to just nine rushing yards. Storme Barton led the Spartans with 195 rushing yards on 13 carries. Dakota Root carried the ball five times for 120 yards for Ridgewood. The Register-Mail
